-- Kenya Bans Powdered Milk Imports to Protect Dairy Industry, Standard Says
-- Sarah McGregor
-- 2010-06-23T06:12:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-23/kenya-bans-powdered-milk-imports-to-protect-dairy-industry-standard-says.html

          
          
             Kenya banned powdered milk imports
To ensure there will no repeat of the oversupply of milk in the
country, a situation which hurt dairy farming earlier this year,
the Standard said, citing Livestock Development Minister
 Mohammed Kuti .  
 The glut forced the East African government to buy 300
million shillings ($3.7 million) of surplus milk stocks to
protect the local dairy industry, the Nairobi-based
newspaper reported.  
